I finally got through to Dr Cree on Monday afternoon and he wants me
to go ahead with the infusion on the 16th &amp; 30th but to be pre-treated
with a gram of Solumedrol the day before and the morning of the
treatment to lower the chances of an allergic reaction.

I'm not thrilled about getting two grams of Solumedrol - I used to
receive 3 grams to deal with exacerbations and the side effects are
very uncomfortable.

But, I'm just focusing on the fact that he thinks I can still take the
Rituximab and that in itself is very good news indeed.

No word on whether or not Blue Shield will pay for the third
treatment , but here's hoping.

Thanks so much for your support my dears!

